data.name: CommandsLabel.Text
data.value:
0 = BRK - Stop the program 1 = JMP - Jump to new position in code 2 = JRF - Jump relative memory slots forward from next number 3 = JRB - Jump relative memory slots back from next number 4 = LDA - Load number into accumulator 5 = STA - Store accumulator into memory slot 6 = LDB - Load backup from memory slot indicated by accumulator 7 = STB - Store backup into memory slot indicated by accumulator 8 = SAV - Save accumulator into backup 9 = SWP - Swap accumulator and backup 10 = ADD - Add value to accumulator 11 = SUB - Subtract value from accumulator 12 = ABK - Add backup to accumulator 13 = SBK - Subtract backup from accumulator 14 = JEZ - Jump to new position if accumulator = 0 15 = JNZ - Jump to new position if accumulator is not equal to 0 16 = JOV - Jump if there was an overflow when adding or subtracting 17 = IN - Get user input as integer (0 - 999) 18 = INT - Export the value of accumulator to the console as integer 19 = CHR - Export the value of accumulator as a text character 20 = BEP - Play a beep sound 21 = RND - Set accumulator to random number from 0 to 999
NOP - Do Nothing (All numbers >21)
